WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.259 --> 00:00:12.053
<i>Checking. One. two.</i>

2
00:00:12.137 --> 00:00:14.931
<i>An announcement to all the residents.</i>

3
00:00:15.015 --> 00:00:17.100
<i>Until 18:00 hours today.</i>

4
00:00:17.183 --> 00:00:20.270
<i>live firearm training</i>
<i>will be conducted on base.</i>

5
00:00:20.979 --> 00:00:23.732
<i>It will cause some dust and noise.</i>

6
00:00:23.815 --> 00:00:26.818
<i>While this may be</i>
<i>an inconvenience to the residents.</i>

7
00:00:27.360 --> 00:00:31.698
<i>this training is for the Armed Forces</i>
<i>who must train for national defense.</i>

8
00:00:31.781 --> 00:00:33.408
<i>Please. keep that in mind.</i>

9
00:00:34.034 --> 00:00:38.496
<i>If you enter the area without permission</i>
<i>while training is in progress.</i>

10
00:00:38.580 --> 00:00:42.333
<i>you could put your lives at risk.</i>

11
00:00:42.417 --> 00:00:45.253
<i>To anyone in the vicinity of the area.</i>

12
00:00:45.336 --> 00:00:49.340
<i>after you have heard this broadcast.</i>

13
00:00:49.424 --> 00:00:51.926
<i>please evacuate to a safe location</i>

14
00:00:52.010 --> 00:00:53.845
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

15
00:01:07.275 --> 00:01:12.197
This is the best weather
to go fishing. Don't you think?

16
00:01:12.280 --> 00:01:15.784
A nice cool cup of <i>makgeolli</i>
would hit the spot right now.

17
00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:40.391
UNDER CONSTRUCTION

18
00:01:40.475 --> 00:01:43.686
RESTRICTED AREA

19
00:02:23.893 --> 00:02:25.728
<i>Group 1. Team 1. Team 2.</i>

20
00:02:25.812 --> 00:02:27.564
<i>The rabbit hunt is about to begin.</i>

21
00:02:28.314 --> 00:02:30.733
<i>Nine hundred and fifty meters</i>
<i>to the rabbit.</i>

22
00:02:34.863 --> 00:02:38.700
Shit. Why are they bitching
from both sides? It's distracting.

23
00:02:39.659 --> 00:02:40.743
Damn.

24
00:03:12.734 --> 00:03:15.570
Jeong Jinman
and his pathetic family portrait.

25
00:03:16.863 --> 00:03:19.157
You've had your share of fun.

26
00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:20.700
You lying bastard.

27
00:04:19.133 --> 00:04:20.134
<i>Focus.</i>

28
00:04:22.345 --> 00:04:24.013
<i>Listen up. Jian.</i>

29
00:04:39.070 --> 00:04:40.238
That's ridiculous.

30
00:04:41.114 --> 00:04:43.324
They can't land a single shot
from both sides?

31
00:04:43.408 --> 00:04:44.409
No. no.

32
00:04:44.909 --> 00:04:46.411
The main character

33
00:04:46.494 --> 00:04:49.747
is using the blind spots really well
to avoid the bullets.

34
00:04:50.498 --> 00:04:53.710
Yeah. right. The movie's over
if the main character dies.

35
00:04:55.169 --> 00:04:56.170
Jeong Jian.

36
00:04:56.754 --> 00:04:57.755
Tell me.

37
00:04:57.839 --> 00:04:58.965
In this very moment.

38
00:04:59.549 --> 00:05:01.926
do you think
you can see everything perfectly?

39
00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:04.637
Yes. of course.

40
00:05:04.721 --> 00:05:06.097
It's right there. Why not?

41
00:05:08.224 --> 00:05:09.350
Oh!

42
00:05:09.726 --> 00:05:11.060
<i>Listen up. Jian.</i>

43
00:05:11.936 --> 00:05:13.855
You're not a dragonfly.

44
00:05:13.938 --> 00:05:17.817
You can't see everything
with the human eye. Don't be mistaken.

45
00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:21.612
There are always blind spots.

46
00:05:22.572 --> 00:05:25.825
If you use those blind spots right
like the guy in the movie does.

47
00:05:25.908 --> 00:05:28.328
you can even survive a fiery pit.

48
00:05:30.371 --> 00:05:31.456
Blind spots.

49
00:06:00.860 --> 00:06:02.570
Jian.

50
00:06:02.653 --> 00:06:04.280
What are you doing?

51
00:06:05.198 --> 00:06:06.282
Well?

52
00:06:20.463 --> 00:06:21.506
What the hell?

53
00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:27.637
Oh. baby girl.

54
00:06:27.720 --> 00:06:30.390
You've watched too many movies.

55
00:06:31.015 --> 00:06:32.600
But too bad.

56
00:06:32.683 --> 00:06:35.395
I'm too far away.

57
00:06:35.895 --> 00:06:36.938
Aren't I?

58
00:06:52.620 --> 00:06:55.289
What are you doing right now?

59
00:07:23.484 --> 00:07:24.819
Shit.

60
00:07:26.571 --> 00:07:28.239
<i>It's flying in from the left side.</i>

61
00:07:29.198 --> 00:07:30.658
<i>A diagonal direction?</i>

62
00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:35.538
<i>The sound of the gunshot came</i>
<i>from much higher and farther away.</i>

63
00:07:56.392 --> 00:07:57.477
What?

64
00:07:58.561 --> 00:08:00.062
Where did she go?

65
00:08:04.442 --> 00:08:05.610
-Hey. Bongo.
-Yes?

66
00:08:05.693 --> 00:08:06.777
Go forward a bit.

67
00:08:06.861 --> 00:08:08.279
Going forward a bit.

68
00:08:31.594 --> 00:08:32.803
What is it?

69
00:08:33.596 --> 00:08:35.264
Are you going to jump from there?

70
00:08:38.184 --> 00:08:39.185
One.

71
00:08:40.228 --> 00:08:41.312
Two.

72
00:08:41.687 --> 00:08:42.688
Three.

73
00:09:12.301 --> 00:09:15.012
Fuck.

74
00:09:33.781 --> 00:09:40.746
A SHOP FOR KILLERS

75
00:09:43.874 --> 00:09:46.002
EPISODE 1
MURTHEHELP

76
00:09:46.085 --> 00:09:48.045
Hey. stop.

77
00:09:48.129 --> 00:09:50.840
-Let go!
-Come on. Take it easy! Easy!

78
00:09:50.923 --> 00:09:52.258
- Officer.
- Yes?

79
00:09:52.341 --> 00:09:54.135
Do you know what happened to me?

80
00:09:54.927 --> 00:09:58.723
Come on. I'm the one that got hit.
She's the one that hit me!

81
00:09:58.806 --> 00:10:01.142
- What?
- I'm telling you. I'm the victim!

82
00:10:01.225 --> 00:10:02.435
- Get up!
- Calm down!

83
00:10:02.518 --> 00:10:04.937
Get up and kick me like you did earlier!

84
00:10:05.021 --> 00:10:08.691
Sir. you're too worked up.
Please calm down. okay?

85
00:10:08.774 --> 00:10:11.611
Excuse me? When can I leave?

86
00:10:11.694 --> 00:10:14.739
We're going to obtain the footage
from the security cameras.

87
00:10:14.822 --> 00:10:16.240
You can leave after that.

88
00:10:16.324 --> 00:10:17.408
But...

89
00:10:18.075 --> 00:10:20.494
- Did you really beat him like that?
- She beat me!

90
00:10:20.578 --> 00:10:23.497
- Calm down so we can hear you.
- What's the problem?

91
00:10:23.581 --> 00:10:26.042
Just let the law punish her.
What's the problem?

92
00:10:26.125 --> 00:10:27.793
- Come on.
- Am I wrong?

93
00:10:34.759 --> 00:10:35.760
What?

94
00:10:42.391 --> 00:10:43.476
What?

95
00:10:56.989 --> 00:10:58.866
What is this?

96
00:10:58.949 --> 00:11:00.242
Can't I go now?

97
00:11:00.326 --> 00:11:01.952
I didn't do anything wrong.

98
00:11:02.036 --> 00:11:04.830
He's the one that came
into the women's restroom.

99
00:11:04.914 --> 00:11:08.709
I'm not saying you did anything wrong.

100
00:11:09.418 --> 00:11:12.588
But you can't just beat up people
like that.

101
00:11:12.672 --> 00:11:14.382
You shouldn't have done that.

102
00:11:14.465 --> 00:11:17.176
We wouldn't have to do this
if you had just held him.

103
00:11:17.885 --> 00:11:21.263
He says he's going to sue you for assault.

104
00:11:21.847 --> 00:11:23.891
But he tried to throw a punch first.

105
00:11:23.974 --> 00:11:27.311
Jian. you can't solve this on your own.

106
00:11:27.395 --> 00:11:30.314
Call your guardian.
You need to settle with him.

107
00:11:31.065 --> 00:11:33.275
Can you call your parents
or a family member?

108
00:11:43.869 --> 00:11:44.954
CALLING JEONG JINMAN

109
00:11:55.172 --> 00:11:57.091
- Hey. Uncle. It's me.
<i>- Ms. Jeong Jian?</i>

110
00:11:58.718 --> 00:11:59.719
Who is this?

111
00:11:59.802 --> 00:12:02.638
<i>This is Park Jinwoo.</i>
<i>from Yecheong Police Station.</i>

112
00:12:02.722 --> 00:12:05.015
<i>I was just about to call you.</i>

113
00:12:05.516 --> 00:12:06.517
Sorry?

114
00:12:07.435 --> 00:12:08.894
Why would the police call me?

115
00:12:10.271 --> 00:12:11.647
<i>Well...</i>

116
00:12:12.481 --> 00:12:14.150
<i>Please don't be too alarmed.</i>

117
00:12:15.192 --> 00:12:16.485
<i>Mr. Jeong Jinman</i>

118
00:12:17.153 --> 00:12:18.446
<i>is dead.</i>

119
00:12:48.800 --> 00:12:51.386
Why install security bars
on the fifth floor?

120
00:12:52.971 --> 00:12:57.016
What kind of crazy thief would climb up
to the fifth floor to steal something?

121
00:12:57.517 --> 00:13:00.061
-I don't even have any money.
-It's done. There.

122
00:13:00.979 --> 00:13:02.146
Also. this closet.

123
00:13:04.482 --> 00:13:06.150
I know you paid for it.

124
00:13:06.234 --> 00:13:08.820
but shouldn't you
have considered my taste?

125
00:13:09.404 --> 00:13:12.073
You really think this suits
a 20-year-old girl's room?

126
00:13:12.573 --> 00:13:13.825
It's retro.

127
00:13:14.283 --> 00:13:15.994
You kids like retro things.

128
00:13:16.619 --> 00:13:17.787
Unbelievable.

129
00:13:18.413 --> 00:13:20.164
Also. take a look at this closet.

130
00:13:20.248 --> 00:13:21.749
It's made of iron. right?

131
00:13:22.458 --> 00:13:23.751
It's bulletproof.

132
00:13:23.835 --> 00:13:25.169
It was very expensive.

133
00:13:26.504 --> 00:13:28.339
What if it rains bullets?

134
00:13:33.136 --> 00:13:35.513
Can you hear me?
It sounds bulletproof. right?

135
00:13:37.932 --> 00:13:39.559
You'll be safe in here.

136
00:13:44.647 --> 00:13:46.524
Why would it rain bullets here?

137
00:13:51.404 --> 00:13:52.447
Forget it.

138
00:13:53.197 --> 00:13:54.198
Just forget it.

139
00:13:59.495 --> 00:14:00.496
Hey. Uncle.

140
00:14:00.997 --> 00:14:04.208
Remember the convenience store owner
who shorted me?

141
00:14:04.292 --> 00:14:08.296
He got into a car accident a few days ago.
He hurt his arms and legs.

142
00:14:08.379 --> 00:14:10.214
He needs six months in the hospital.

143
00:14:10.882 --> 00:14:14.385
I don't know what the accident did to him.

144
00:14:14.469 --> 00:14:18.014
but he called and said he'd wire me
all the money he didn't pay me.

145
00:14:18.097 --> 00:14:20.600
And not just me but all the part-timers.

146
00:14:20.683 --> 00:14:21.768
Isn't that crazy?

147
00:14:24.145 --> 00:14:25.605
I was so pissed back then.

148
00:14:25.688 --> 00:14:27.857
JEONG JIAN
KYUNGSEO UNIVERSITY

149
00:14:27.940 --> 00:14:31.486
I did what you taught me and shouted
your name at the sky three times.

150
00:14:31.569 --> 00:14:33.946
-I think that really worked.
-Right.

151
00:14:35.073 --> 00:14:36.324
I did that.

152
00:14:36.824 --> 00:14:38.159
I broke his arms and legs.

153
00:14:42.455 --> 00:14:43.498
Uncle.

154
00:14:45.041 --> 00:14:47.794
You have a lot of scars on your face.

155
00:14:47.877 --> 00:14:49.629
so you have the face of a criminal.

156
00:14:50.338 --> 00:14:52.590
You can't joke around like that.

157
00:14:59.388 --> 00:15:01.641
Why are you taking pictures of this?

158
00:15:03.184 --> 00:15:04.852
Why are you crossing the line?

159
00:15:05.812 --> 00:15:09.482
When a soldier dies in a war.
they lodge their dog tag between the teeth

160
00:15:09.982 --> 00:15:12.652
to remember their service number.

161
00:15:12.735 --> 00:15:16.489
Your registration number follows you
from birth to death.

162
00:15:16.572 --> 00:15:19.242
It means that the number given to you

163
00:15:19.325 --> 00:15:21.077
is very. very important.

164
00:15:21.702 --> 00:15:23.121
What are you talking about?

165
00:15:24.247 --> 00:15:29.043
It's the same with your school ID number.
Make sure you never forget it.

166
00:15:29.585 --> 00:15:31.587
2-2-0-1-9-0-7-4.

167
00:15:33.339 --> 00:15:35.133
Memorize the number all of a sudden?

168
00:15:35.216 --> 00:15:37.802
2-2-0-1-9-0-7-4.

169
00:15:37.885 --> 00:15:40.471
2-2-0-1-9-0-7-4.

170
00:15:41.764 --> 00:15:44.058
2-2-0-1-9-0-7-4.

171
00:15:48.521 --> 00:15:50.189
The last thing he said to me

172
00:15:51.440 --> 00:15:52.733
is my school ID number.

173
00:15:58.573 --> 00:15:59.907
I was just wondering...

174
00:15:59.991 --> 00:16:02.326
You're Jinman's niece. aren't you?

175
00:16:03.744 --> 00:16:05.788
I'm a friend of Jinman.

176
00:16:05.872 --> 00:16:07.832
We went to the same middle
and high school.

177
00:16:08.416 --> 00:16:11.294
I saw you a few times
when you were younger.

178
00:16:11.377 --> 00:16:13.087
I don't know if you remember me.

179
00:16:14.463 --> 00:16:17.091
Oh... Hello.

180
00:16:17.175 --> 00:16:19.385
Hi to you too.

181
00:16:19.468 --> 00:16:22.263
Wow! You got so big!

182
00:16:22.346 --> 00:16:25.725
I heard you attend school in Seoul.
Are you visiting your uncle?

183
00:16:25.808 --> 00:16:28.102
So. how is Jinman?

184
00:16:29.854 --> 00:16:31.397
He's dead.

185
00:16:37.278 --> 00:16:40.114
Don't hold the funeral here.

186
00:16:40.698 --> 00:16:42.867
The funeral home
at that intersection is better.

187
00:16:42.950 --> 00:16:45.411
This place is big.
but it's lousy on the inside.

188
00:16:45.494 --> 00:16:47.997
I'll call an employee I know
that works there.

189
00:16:48.080 --> 00:16:50.333
Once you book the room... Hold on.

190
00:16:52.418 --> 00:16:53.586
This is my card.

191
00:16:54.295 --> 00:16:55.546
Call me at this number.

192
00:16:58.424 --> 00:17:00.009
Don't worry too much.

193
00:17:01.260 --> 00:17:02.303
Thank you.

194
00:17:08.059 --> 00:17:12.104
HANSARANG GYUNGAE HOSPITAL

195
00:17:52.937 --> 00:17:55.773
Right. we'll verify
the identity of the body now.

196
00:17:55.856 --> 00:17:58.067
Is this Mr. Jeong Jinman?

197
00:17:59.777 --> 00:18:00.861
But I was wondering...

198
00:18:02.405 --> 00:18:06.534
When people commit suicide.
don't they normally slit their wrists?

199
00:18:08.244 --> 00:18:09.328
He was alone.

200
00:18:11.372 --> 00:18:13.833
How did he cut his throat like this?

201
00:18:14.375 --> 00:18:15.626
Yes. we investigated it

202
00:18:15.710 --> 00:18:19.630
as a possible homicide due to his injury.

203
00:18:20.256 --> 00:18:22.466
but no one was caught
on the security cameras

204
00:18:22.550 --> 00:18:24.093
around his house for a week.

205
00:18:24.844 --> 00:18:27.179
Also. according to the autopsy report.

206
00:18:27.263 --> 00:18:29.181
judging by the angle of the wound.

207
00:18:29.265 --> 00:18:31.726
it could have been made by himself.

208
00:18:31.809 --> 00:18:34.312
So we have concluded
that it was a suicide.

209
00:18:35.479 --> 00:18:38.232
If you want.
I can send you the autopsy report.

210
00:18:40.401 --> 00:18:42.320
It's just like him to die like this.

211
00:18:44.113 --> 00:18:45.114
Excuse me?

212
00:18:45.740 --> 00:18:47.325
His death suits him.

213
00:18:49.952 --> 00:18:51.037
No.

214
00:18:51.120 --> 00:18:52.913
I don't need the autopsy report.

215
00:18:55.916 --> 00:18:58.627
Okay. That confirms
the identity of the body.

216
00:18:58.711 --> 00:19:01.130
We'll proceed with the handover procedure.

217
00:19:01.213 --> 00:19:04.175
Sign here. and it will be complete.

218
00:19:11.349 --> 00:19:13.309
Then. the handover procedure

219
00:19:13.392 --> 00:19:15.394
is now complete.

220
00:19:28.449 --> 00:19:30.493
There are two types of mourning clothes.

221
00:19:30.576 --> 00:19:33.329
This is the common set.
and this is the modern hanbok.

222
00:19:33.412 --> 00:19:35.289
You can pick between the two.

223
00:19:42.380 --> 00:19:44.256
<i>Did my uncle</i>
<i>always have that tattoo?</i>

224
00:19:53.557 --> 00:19:56.352
Miss! You can't smoke in here!

225
00:19:58.229 --> 00:19:59.230
Oh...

226
00:20:00.106 --> 00:20:01.524
I'm sorry.

227
00:20:03.734 --> 00:20:06.237
Anyway. let me go over it again.

228
00:20:06.821 --> 00:20:08.531
You need to pick a mourning suit.

229
00:20:09.198 --> 00:20:12.076
-Here's the hairpin...
-I'm the chief mourner.

230
00:20:12.618 --> 00:20:14.036
What about the armband?

231
00:20:15.287 --> 00:20:18.457
Oh. normally men wear the armbands.

232
00:20:18.541 --> 00:20:21.794
Do you have any close male relatives?

233
00:20:21.877 --> 00:20:23.295
No. there's no one.

234
00:20:24.004 --> 00:20:25.297
Oh...

235
00:20:26.424 --> 00:20:29.510
Well. the most important thing
is the portrait of the deceased.

236
00:20:29.593 --> 00:20:31.887
Do you have a picture of the deceased?

237
00:21:08.465 --> 00:21:09.466
Jeong Jian?

238
00:21:14.387 --> 00:21:15.388
It is you.

239
00:21:19.350 --> 00:21:20.351
Do you remember me?

240
00:21:20.935 --> 00:21:21.936
Bae Jeongmin.

241
00:21:24.105 --> 00:21:25.106
Huh?

242
00:21:28.776 --> 00:21:30.111
Are you okay?

243
00:21:35.450 --> 00:21:38.953
Yeah. I remember you. Bae Jeongmin.

244
00:21:46.920 --> 00:21:49.672
We can cut out the picture
of your uncle's face

245
00:21:49.756 --> 00:21:51.299
and stick it on like this.

246
00:21:59.015 --> 00:22:00.016
Oh.

247
00:22:00.558 --> 00:22:02.185
I major in computer engineering.

248
00:22:03.019 --> 00:22:04.020
This is easy.

249
00:22:05.522 --> 00:22:06.648
I see.

250
00:22:08.650 --> 00:22:10.777
That's how I came to help your uncle.

251
00:22:11.361 --> 00:22:15.114
After the military service.
I came back home

252
00:22:15.198 --> 00:22:18.117
and saw your uncle's notice
looking for part-time help.

253
00:22:19.369 --> 00:22:23.498
He was trying to revamp
his agricultural hose sales website.

254
00:22:24.958 --> 00:22:27.252
So I was working on it for a few days.

255
00:22:30.004 --> 00:22:31.005
During that time...

256
00:22:33.841 --> 00:22:36.761
your uncle passed away.

257
00:22:38.596 --> 00:22:39.764
That's why

258
00:22:39.847 --> 00:22:42.183
I was the last person to contact him.

259
00:22:43.726 --> 00:22:46.104
And I'm the one the police called first.

260
00:22:47.897 --> 00:22:49.440
I don't know what to say...

261
00:22:50.984 --> 00:22:53.069
I don't know how to console you.

262
00:22:57.407 --> 00:23:00.368
Your uncle was found
in the bathroom. right?

263
00:23:01.244 --> 00:23:02.745
Have you cleaned it up?

264
00:23:05.540 --> 00:23:06.874
No. not yet.

265
00:23:10.545 --> 00:23:11.546
Jian.

266
00:23:12.463 --> 00:23:13.715
If it's too hard for you.

267
00:23:14.340 --> 00:23:16.301
do you want me to clean it up?

268
00:23:17.969 --> 00:23:20.138
Your uncle and I were pretty close.

269
00:23:20.221 --> 00:23:22.265
I think it'll be okay for me to do it.

270
00:23:33.276 --> 00:23:34.360
I would

271
00:23:35.069 --> 00:23:36.279
really appreciate it.

272
00:23:37.697 --> 00:23:40.908
Sure. I'll clean up the bathroom.

273
00:23:40.992 --> 00:23:43.161
Don't worry. and take care of his funeral.

274
00:23:43.244 --> 00:23:44.621
I'll go after I'm done.

275
00:23:45.371 --> 00:23:47.540
Thanks. Jeongmin.

276
00:23:57.008 --> 00:23:58.259
Jian.

277
00:24:00.303 --> 00:24:03.056
I brought Jinman's childhood friends.

278
00:24:16.152 --> 00:24:19.781
Make sure to remember all of this.
You have to pay them back one day.

279
00:24:19.864 --> 00:24:21.574
The gym at Yecheong Intersection.

280
00:24:21.658 --> 00:24:24.869
The owner is the president
of Yecheong High Alumni Association.

281
00:24:24.952 --> 00:24:27.580
This is from Yecheon Middle School
Alumni Association.

282
00:24:27.664 --> 00:24:30.083
Also. this is from Lee Yonghan.

283
00:24:31.042 --> 00:24:32.043
COMRADE LEE YONGHAN

284
00:24:32.126 --> 00:24:34.462
I don't really know who this is.

285
00:24:35.296 --> 00:24:36.714
You have a guest!

286
00:24:36.798 --> 00:24:38.716
-Miss. come here.
-Okay.

287
00:24:38.800 --> 00:24:41.219
I'll take care of things here.

288
00:24:41.302 --> 00:24:43.012
Go and greet the guests.

289
00:24:43.096 --> 00:24:44.097
Mmm.

290
00:24:44.639 --> 00:24:48.726
COMRADE LEE YONGHAN

291
00:24:50.645 --> 00:24:51.938
Are you okay?

292
00:24:52.021 --> 00:24:53.856
I'm fine. but...

293
00:25:12.399 --> 00:25:13.483
Jeong.

294
00:25:14.067 --> 00:25:15.652
So this is how you go.

295
00:25:17.321 --> 00:25:19.281
I'll see you later in hell.

296
00:25:29.291 --> 00:25:31.585
Do you need anything else?

297
00:25:32.294 --> 00:25:34.254
We have pancakes. Do you want some?

298
00:25:38.383 --> 00:25:41.803
So you were colleagues of Jinman. right?

299
00:25:44.556 --> 00:25:45.641
All right.

300
00:25:47.476 --> 00:25:49.227
Wow.

301
00:25:51.938 --> 00:25:55.067
What a bunch of rude jerks.

302
00:25:55.150 --> 00:25:57.569
They should respond
when someone talks to them.

303
00:25:57.653 --> 00:26:00.238
Aren't those twins from the neighborhood?

304
00:26:00.322 --> 00:26:02.574
Come on. I know everyone
in this neighborhood.

305
00:26:02.658 --> 00:26:05.410
They're all outsiders.

306
00:26:54.626 --> 00:26:57.921
Jinman!

307
00:26:59.548 --> 00:27:02.843
What's with him? Did Jinman
owe him money or something?

308
00:27:03.635 --> 00:27:05.303
Or did he date Jinman?

309
00:27:06.012 --> 00:27:08.014
He's been crying like that for two days.

310
00:27:08.098 --> 00:27:09.975
That's what I'm saying.

311
00:27:11.101 --> 00:27:12.602
By the way.

312
00:27:12.686 --> 00:27:14.312
why did Jinman commit suicide?

313
00:27:14.396 --> 00:27:17.733
You know. he was selling
those hoses on the Internet.

314
00:27:18.358 --> 00:27:19.818
I think it wasn't going well.

315
00:27:20.610 --> 00:27:21.987
He had a lot of debt.

316
00:27:22.070 --> 00:27:24.865
Money's always the problem.

317
00:27:24.948 --> 00:27:27.200
If that was the case.
why didn't you help him?

318
00:27:27.284 --> 00:27:29.327
You run seven greenhouses!

319
00:27:29.411 --> 00:27:30.829
Why should I?

320
00:27:30.912 --> 00:27:32.873
I've never liked Jinman.

321
00:27:32.956 --> 00:27:35.876
That's because you got your ass handed
to you by Jinman

322
00:27:35.959 --> 00:27:37.961
when he caught you robbing younger kids.

323
00:27:38.044 --> 00:27:39.588
-No. I didn't!
-Yes. you did.

324
00:27:40.213 --> 00:27:43.508
Jinman knocked out three of your teeth!
I saw it!

325
00:27:46.052 --> 00:27:49.181
Jinman was so popular back then.

326
00:27:49.723 --> 00:27:51.850
Hey! Did you hear?

327
00:27:52.350 --> 00:27:54.936
Before Jinman came back home.

328
00:27:55.020 --> 00:27:57.230
he was the leader of Mokpo's Wasp Gang.

329
00:27:57.814 --> 00:28:00.525
What the hell are you talking about?

330
00:28:00.609 --> 00:28:02.235
Jinman was not a gangster.

331
00:28:02.319 --> 00:28:03.570
It's true! The Wasp Gang!

332
00:28:03.653 --> 00:28:06.031
You don't know anything at all!

333
00:28:07.282 --> 00:28:10.827
This is a real secret
that only few people know.

334
00:28:11.703 --> 00:28:12.704
There's a rumor...

335
00:28:15.081 --> 00:28:18.627
that Jinman was
an anti-North spy for the NIS.

336
00:28:19.294 --> 00:28:20.545
What a load of crock.

337
00:28:20.629 --> 00:28:23.340
What you just said
is absolutely ridiculous.

338
00:28:23.423 --> 00:28:25.759
He got terrible grades at school!

339
00:28:25.842 --> 00:28:27.469
He pretty much got straight F's!

340
00:28:27.552 --> 00:28:28.762
F. F. F. F. F!

341
00:28:28.845 --> 00:28:31.556
How could he have joined the NIS
with his grades?

342
00:28:31.640 --> 00:28:33.099
Special employment. man!

343
00:28:33.183 --> 00:28:35.602
-The Wasp Gang!
-I'm right!

344
00:28:35.685 --> 00:28:37.604
You bastards!

345
00:28:37.687 --> 00:28:39.189
You scared me. What the hell?

346
00:28:39.272 --> 00:28:40.690
-What?
-What the hell?

347
00:28:40.774 --> 00:28:42.651
You little punks!

348
00:28:43.401 --> 00:28:45.987
You shouldn't speak like that!

349
00:28:46.905 --> 00:28:50.659
Don't you remember who Jinman was to us?

350
00:28:50.742 --> 00:28:54.538
Do you remember
when our dads lost all their money

351
00:28:54.621 --> 00:28:57.582
to the gambling house
in the neighborhood over?

352
00:28:57.666 --> 00:28:59.584
Why would you bring that up now?

353
00:28:59.668 --> 00:29:01.795
Your dad lost tens of millions of won.

354
00:29:01.878 --> 00:29:03.797
My dad lost the deed to the house.

355
00:29:03.880 --> 00:29:06.174
He came home and lit briquettes.

356
00:29:06.258 --> 00:29:08.510
<i>My brother and I almost died!</i>

357
00:29:09.177 --> 00:29:10.846
Back then.

358
00:29:10.929 --> 00:29:15.183
I inhaled the smoke and almost died!

359
00:29:15.851 --> 00:29:16.977
Back then!

360
00:29:24.693 --> 00:29:25.777
Jinman?

361
00:29:31.283 --> 00:29:32.826
<i>It was definitely him.</i>

362
00:29:36.705 --> 00:29:38.456
It was Jinman that left the money?

363
00:29:39.124 --> 00:29:42.836
Jinman was the one that saved you all.

364
00:29:46.673 --> 00:29:48.425
Jinman. you bastard.

365
00:29:57.017 --> 00:29:58.768
<i>I lived with him for ten years.</i>

366
00:30:00.228 --> 00:30:01.771
<i>But I know nothing about him.</i>

367
00:31:27.231 --> 00:31:29.191
We'll leave after you're done smoking.

368
00:31:40.452 --> 00:31:41.537
Jian.

369
00:31:43.747 --> 00:31:45.499
I'll go to the cemetery with you.

370
00:32:02.224 --> 00:32:04.309
She didn't cry once at the funeral.

371
00:32:04.810 --> 00:32:07.187
Maybe she wasn't that attached to him.

372
00:32:07.271 --> 00:32:08.564
Maybe they weren't close.

373
00:32:08.647 --> 00:32:11.608
Oh. stop it. She can hear you.

374
00:32:15.404 --> 00:32:16.822
They're unbelievable.

375
00:32:18.532 --> 00:32:21.035
People all mourn in different ways.

376
00:32:25.039 --> 00:32:26.457
Great job. Jian.

377
00:32:40.471 --> 00:32:42.681
I cleaned up the bathroom for you.

378
00:32:42.765 --> 00:32:43.807
Okay.

379
00:32:45.559 --> 00:32:46.894
Thanks. Jeongmin.

380
00:32:47.811 --> 00:32:49.563
It's nothing. I'm glad I could be of help.

381
00:32:50.064 --> 00:32:51.190
We were close as kids.

382
00:32:53.108 --> 00:32:54.109
I'm relieved

383
00:32:54.860 --> 00:32:57.196
you're coping better than I thought.

384
00:32:59.531 --> 00:33:00.616
Does it look like

385
00:33:01.450 --> 00:33:04.244
I'm holding it together to you?

386
00:33:06.580 --> 00:33:07.581
Well...

387
00:33:08.707 --> 00:33:09.792
Are you not?

388
00:33:13.670 --> 00:33:15.547
I'm disgusted with my uncle.

389
00:33:17.007 --> 00:33:18.217
The way he died.

390
00:33:27.267 --> 00:33:28.811
Sorry. I shouldn't say that.

391
00:33:30.646 --> 00:33:31.730
Thanks a lot.

392
00:33:32.231 --> 00:33:33.732
Once I pull myself together.

393
00:33:33.816 --> 00:33:35.943
I'll call you. Let's grab a bite to eat.

394
00:33:38.237 --> 00:33:39.238
Sure.

395
00:33:39.738 --> 00:33:41.031
Make sure to call. Jian.

396
00:33:42.157 --> 00:33:43.158
Bye.

397
00:35:48.408 --> 00:35:49.910
<i>I already ate.</i>

398
00:35:57.334 --> 00:35:58.919
Make yourself something to eat.

399
00:36:41.253 --> 00:36:42.796
What was so hard for you?

400
00:36:46.925 --> 00:36:48.719
What was so hard for you?

401
00:36:52.931 --> 00:36:54.891
You pretended to be so strong.

402
00:37:01.732 --> 00:37:03.900
What am I supposed to do all alone now?

403
00:37:15.329 --> 00:37:17.748
Jian. I forgot to give you...

404
00:37:18.957 --> 00:37:20.042
this...

405
00:37:26.048 --> 00:37:28.300
Should I come back later?

406
00:37:36.933 --> 00:37:37.934
Jeongmin.

407
00:37:40.187 --> 00:37:41.355
Yes?

408
00:37:41.855 --> 00:37:43.940
I'm not doing okay right now.

409
00:37:48.070 --> 00:37:50.155
Can you stay with me for a little while?

410
00:38:27.983 --> 00:38:29.610
Thanks again. Jeongmin.

411
00:38:30.945 --> 00:38:32.446
No. don't mention it.

412
00:38:33.197 --> 00:38:35.449
I don't have anything to do
at home anyway.

413
00:38:36.033 --> 00:38:38.160
I can stay longer.

414
00:38:38.244 --> 00:38:39.328
Okay.

415
00:38:41.705 --> 00:38:42.832
Right.

416
00:38:44.375 --> 00:38:46.043
You found this in the bathroom?

417
00:38:47.336 --> 00:38:49.713
Yes. I think it was your uncle's.

418
00:38:50.798 --> 00:38:51.841
No. it's not.

419
00:38:52.341 --> 00:38:55.845
We both got the latest models
when I started college.

420
00:38:58.931 --> 00:39:00.391
Can this even make calls?

421
00:39:02.226 --> 00:39:06.021
Or maybe your uncle used it for work?

422
00:39:06.105 --> 00:39:08.107
What. like a burner phone?

423
00:39:13.696 --> 00:39:16.323
I DEPOSITED 70 MILLION WON!
WHEN CAN I RECEIVE THE ITEM?

424
00:39:16.407 --> 00:39:17.408
Seventy million won?

425
00:39:19.869 --> 00:39:22.496
How many hoses did they buy
to deposit that much?

426
00:39:25.499 --> 00:39:28.043
18.753.000.000 WON

427
00:39:36.010 --> 00:39:37.011
Jeongmin.

428
00:39:38.179 --> 00:39:39.263
How much is this?

429
00:39:43.392 --> 00:39:44.477
Eighteen...

430
00:39:45.227 --> 00:39:46.645
18.7 billion won?

431
00:39:55.738 --> 00:39:58.908
Do you think you can earn this much
from selling hoses?

432
00:40:00.701 --> 00:40:01.702
No.

433
00:40:08.751 --> 00:40:11.921
The website that you revamped
for my uncle.

434
00:40:12.421 --> 00:40:13.506
Can you show me?

435
00:40:16.592 --> 00:40:18.928
70 million won's worth of these hoses?

436
00:40:20.179 --> 00:40:22.014
It's a little over 11 kilometers.

437
00:40:23.599 --> 00:40:24.975
As you said.

438
00:40:25.059 --> 00:40:28.729
it doesn't make sense to order
that much money's worth of hoses.

439
00:40:29.313 --> 00:40:30.314
Right.

440
00:40:33.776 --> 00:40:34.860
But...

441
00:40:35.611 --> 00:40:39.573
if this website was used
as a front for a different website...

442
00:40:44.161 --> 00:40:45.246
WE CAN'T FIND THE PAGE

443
00:40:59.927 --> 00:41:01.053
This...

444
00:41:09.562 --> 00:41:11.355
YOU HAVE LOGGED IN AUTOMATICALLY

445
00:41:18.362 --> 00:41:20.239
-It's the dark web.
-What?

446
00:41:21.365 --> 00:41:22.575
An illegal website.

447
00:41:23.200 --> 00:41:25.869
The agricultural goods website
is probably a front.

448
00:41:26.412 --> 00:41:28.789
Like a passageway to this website.

449
00:41:28.872 --> 00:41:30.708
Then. what kind of website is this?

450
00:41:33.794 --> 00:41:36.297
There are prices to the weapons here.

451
00:41:39.425 --> 00:41:42.344
It looks like a website
that sells weapons.

452
00:41:43.137 --> 00:41:44.221
Weapons?

453
00:41:49.101 --> 00:41:50.561
He sold things like this?

454
00:41:51.687 --> 00:41:52.730
My uncle?

455
00:41:53.647 --> 00:41:54.648
Yes.

456
00:42:02.406 --> 00:42:04.241
I PAID. WHEN WILL YOU SHIP IT?

457
00:42:22.885 --> 00:42:24.928
I AM SORRY. THE SHOP WILL BE CLOSED...

458
00:42:26.513 --> 00:42:29.350
I'LL RETURN YOUR MONEY
IF YOU PROVIDE YOUR ACCOUNT NUMBER

459
00:42:32.686 --> 00:42:34.605
THEN... IS JEONG JINMAN DEAD?

460
00:42:37.566 --> 00:42:39.276
THEN... YOU'LL DIE TODAY TOO. JIAN

461
00:42:45.282 --> 00:42:47.368
What a crazy bastard!

462
00:42:48.118 --> 00:42:50.120
Jian. don't let this bother you.

463
00:42:50.204 --> 00:42:51.455
This person is crazy.

464
00:42:56.543 --> 00:42:58.712
Still. just to be safe.

465
00:42:59.463 --> 00:43:00.714
shall we call the police?

466
00:43:20.901 --> 00:43:23.028
Jinman. it's Minhye.

467
00:43:28.200 --> 00:43:30.411
My uncle isn't home today.

468
00:43:30.494 --> 00:43:32.037
Please come back next time.

469
00:43:33.038 --> 00:43:35.582
<i>"Uncle"? You must be his niece.</i>

470
00:43:35.666 --> 00:43:37.835
<i>Wow. I heard a lot about you.</i>

471
00:43:37.918 --> 00:43:42.005
I'm So Minhye.
Jinman's private Chinese tutor.

472
00:43:42.089 --> 00:43:44.133
Anyway. did Jinman go somewhere?

473
00:43:44.675 --> 00:43:46.552
We have a lesson today.

474
00:43:46.635 --> 00:43:49.596
<i>I called. but I can't get through to him.</i>

475
00:43:49.680 --> 00:43:50.806
As you know.

476
00:43:50.889 --> 00:43:54.476
he's not the type to change plans
without calling ahead.

477
00:43:55.436 --> 00:43:57.229
My uncle was learning Chinese?

478
00:44:04.278 --> 00:44:06.071
DON'T LET ANYONE ELSE KILL YOU

479
00:44:06.155 --> 00:44:08.073
I'LL COME AND KILL YOU MYSELF. JIAN.

480
00:44:13.871 --> 00:44:16.957
Your front door was open. so I came in.

481
00:44:19.209 --> 00:44:20.586
If it's all right with you.

482
00:44:20.669 --> 00:44:23.297
can I wait for him inside?

483
00:44:41.273 --> 00:44:46.028
A SHOP FOR KILLERS

484
00:44:46.111 --> 00:44:47.112
JIAN
7 YEARS OLD

485
00:44:47.196 --> 00:44:50.240
I would've prepared something
had I known you were coming.

486
00:44:50.324 --> 00:44:52.993
What's there to prepare?
We'll eat whatever you serve.

487
00:44:53.994 --> 00:44:55.996
You come and sit too.

488
00:44:56.121 --> 00:44:57.915
Yes. come and sit.

489
00:44:59.166 --> 00:45:00.250
Is it good?

490
00:45:01.251 --> 00:45:02.252
Does it taste good?

491
00:45:03.045 --> 00:45:04.546
It must be really good.

492
00:45:04.630 --> 00:45:06.673
You shoved all of that down your throat.

493
00:45:07.341 --> 00:45:09.468
You sure know how to stuff your face.

494
00:45:09.551 --> 00:45:11.345
- Stop that.
- It's good.

495
00:45:12.429 --> 00:45:16.391
You know how good our food is.
Why haven't you come by more often?

496
00:45:17.017 --> 00:45:18.977
Wait a second. How long has it been?

497
00:45:19.520 --> 00:45:20.521
Mom.

498
00:45:21.230 --> 00:45:24.775
-Has it been five or six years?
-Seven years and eight months.

499
00:45:26.235 --> 00:45:27.528
Almost eight years.

500
00:45:28.487 --> 00:45:30.364
My God. little brother.

501
00:45:30.447 --> 00:45:33.033
You haven't called or visited us
for eight years?

502
00:45:34.034 --> 00:45:35.828
Since I didn't hear from you once.

503
00:45:35.911 --> 00:45:39.581
I figured you were on a boat somewhere
and died at sea.

504
00:45:39.665 --> 00:45:41.124
- You know?
- Goodness.

505
00:45:41.208 --> 00:45:42.501
Stop that!

506
00:45:44.670 --> 00:45:46.296
Honey. that's enough.

507
00:45:47.673 --> 00:45:49.591
Jinman. do you want more meat?

508
00:45:49.675 --> 00:45:50.759
Yes. please.

509
00:45:51.301 --> 00:45:52.594
What happened to your face?

510
00:45:53.428 --> 00:45:56.181
-Did you get into a fight?
-No. it's just a scratch.

511
00:45:57.182 --> 00:45:58.600
You should be more careful.

512
00:45:59.142 --> 00:46:00.227
My son.

513
00:46:00.727 --> 00:46:03.230
-You need to get married.
-Yeah. right!

514
00:46:03.313 --> 00:46:05.107
Look at this bum. Mom!

515
00:46:05.190 --> 00:46:06.900
Women would run away from him!

516
00:46:06.984 --> 00:46:09.486
- Damn it.
- Stop it. honey.

517
00:46:13.448 --> 00:46:15.367
- Jeong Jian.
- That's my girl.

518
00:46:24.418 --> 00:46:26.628
Do you know my name?

519
00:46:27.170 --> 00:46:28.171
I don't.

520
00:46:28.755 --> 00:46:30.048
Jeong Jinman.

521
00:46:30.799 --> 00:46:32.050
It's Jeong Jinman.

522
00:46:32.134 --> 00:46:33.135
Remember it.

523
00:46:35.888 --> 00:46:36.972
My baby.
